10/05/2011
PODGORICA, Montenegro -- Four people accused of murdering senior police official Slavoljub Scekic were sentenced on Monday (May 9th) to a total of 120 years in prison.
Scekic was gunned down outside his home in Podgorica in August 2005.
Sasa Boreta and Ljubo Bigovic got 30 years each for masterminding the killing, while Milan Scekic and Ljubo Vujadinovic were sentenced to 30 years each as perpetrators.
(RTCG, Pcnen - 09/05/11)
